{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"697bda27-b133-411a-90b7-6ba6a31c9c7d","content":"The working directory is empty — no existing files to modify. Here's the configuration you need:\n\n## Environment Variables for Your Container\n\nFor NativeAOT on .NET 11, set these env vars so the runtime invokes `createdump` on crash:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  # Enable crash dump collection (1 = mini, 2 = heap, 3 = triage, 4 = full)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  # Path to createdump since NativeAOT doesn't bundle it\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n  - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"\n  - name: DOTNET_EnableCrashReport\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n```\n\n## Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... existing image, ports, etc.\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"                          # Full dump — use \"1\" for mini\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n        - name: DOTNET_EnableCrashReport\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n          value: \"1\"\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dump-volume\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n      securityContext:\n        # createdump needs ptrace to capture the dump\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]\n  volumes:\n    - name: dump-volume\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi          # adjust based on your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Setting | Why |\n|---|---|\n| **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** | Required for NativeAOT — the runtime doesn't ship `createdump` itself |\n| **`SYS_PTRACE` capability** | `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process |\n| **`emptyDir` volume** | Keeps dumps off the container's overlay FS; swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts |\n| **`%e.%p.%t` pattern** | Produces filenames like `myapp.42.1715475600.dmp` (executable, PID, timestamp) |\n\nTo retrieve dumps from a running pod: `kubectl cp <pod>:/tmp/dumps ./local-dumps`. For production, consider replacing `emptyDir` with a PVC or a sidecar that ships dumps to blob storage.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9c240b75-9854-4c5d-ade5-9f82ff70189e","outputTokens":810,"requestId":"1B91:39DF49:DBF131:FB5980:6A028699"},"id":"c816fe92-feb2-4226-b6df-907db614d332","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:47:20.244Z","parentId":"d78a0ce9-3d7c-4bfa-9de6-86f8c76ad630"}
